This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories, as it deals with the relationship between Evolution Strategies and Finite Differences in the context of Reinforcement Learning. It may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories, as well as Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), given the use of the MNIST classification problem as a benchmark.
